---

<BaseLayout
  title="The Curriculum — Power In Numbers"
  description="PINU. The eight-phase Methodology Map and Entrepreneurial Timeline. Eight courses, each paired with a discrete business-plan deliverable. The formation discipline that produces cartographers."
>
  <PageHero
    eyebrow="Methodology · Layer 02"
    headline="The Curriculum"
    lede="An eight-phase development sequence. Eight courses. One business plan, built piece by piece. The formation discipline that converts an operator into a cartographer."
    metaLeft="PINU"
    metaRight="Rev 8-25-05 · current canon"
  />

  {/* ──────────────────────────────────────────────
      §01 — What the curriculum is
      ────────────────────────────────────────────── */}
  <section class="section">
    <div class="frame">
      <SectionMarker num="§ 01" tag="What it is" />

      <h2 class="s-title" data-reveal>
        Eight phases. Eight courses. One audited plan.
      </h2>

      <div class="prose" data-reveal>
        <p>
          PINU is the curriculum side of Power In Numbers&rsquo; methodology &mdash;
          the formation discipline that produces operators capable of running
          decision cartography in the field. It is taught as eight sequential
          phases. Each phase is a course; each course resolves a specific
          development question; each course produces a specific section of
          a defensible business plan.
        </p>
        <p>
          The curriculum is not a survey. It is a working sequence. The order
          is the argument. An operator does not earn the right to study
          phase three until phase two is closed; does not earn the right
          to enter phase six until phase five has produced a documented
          management plan. The Methodology Map is the timeline that
          enforces the order.
        </p>
        <p>
          The deliverable produced across the eight phases is a single,
          finalized business plan, written in pieces, audited at each
          phase, and stress-tested by the validation layer at the end.
          What the operator carries forward at graduation is the plan,
          the discipline that produced it, and the operating habit
          of writing every assertion in a form a third party can audit.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* ──────────────────────────────────────────────
      §02 — The eight-phase map
      ────────────────────────────────────────────── */}
  <section class="section section--paper-deep">
    <div class="frame">
      <SectionMarker num="§ 02" tag="The map" />

      <h2 class="s-title" data-reveal>
        The Methodology Map and Entrepreneurial Timeline.
      </h2>
      <p class="s-lede" data-reveal>
        The phases run left to right. Each is a working course. The map is
        read in sequence; phases are not selectable.
      </p>

      <ol class="map" data-reveal aria-label="PINU — eight-phase development curriculum">
        {phases.map((p) => (
          <li class="map__cell">
            <a href={`#phase-${p.num}`} class="map__link">
              <span class="map__num">Phase {p.num}</span>
              <span class="map__name">{p.short}</span>
            </a>
          </li>
        ))}
      </ol>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* ──────────────────────────────────────────────
      §03 — The eight phases in full
      ────────────────────────────────────────────── */}
  <section class="section">
    <div class="frame">
      <SectionMarker num="§ 03" tag="The eight phases in full" />

      <div class="phases">
        {phases.map((p) => (
          <article class="phase" id={`phase-${p.num}`}>
            <header class="phase__head">
              <div class="phase__index">
                <span class="phase__num">Phase {p.num}</span>
                <span class="phase__course">Course {p.num}</span>
              </div>
              <h3 class="phase__name">{p.title}</h3>
              <p class="phase__resolves">
                <span class="phase__resolves-label">Resolves.</span> {p.resolves}
              </p>
            </header>

            <p class="phase__body" set:html={p.body}></p>

            <div class="phase__detail">
              <div class="phase__sub phase__sub--topics">
                <p class="phase__sub-label">Topic detail</p>
                <ul class="phase__topics">
                  {p.topics.map((t) => (<li>{t}</li>))}
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div class="phase__sub phase__sub--bizplan">
                <p class="phase__sub-label">{p.bizPlan.label}</p>
                <ul class="phase__bizplan">
                  {p.bizPlan.pieces.map((piece) => (<li>{piece}</li>))}
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </article>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* ──────────────────────────────────────────────
      §04 — Curriculum × framework × validation
      ────────────────────────────────────────────── */}
  <section class="section section--paper-deep">
    <div class="frame">
      <SectionMarker num="§ 04" tag="How the layers couple" />

      <h2 class="s-title" data-reveal>
        The curriculum forms the cartographer.
      </h2>
      <p class="s-lede" data-reveal>
        PINU does not exist in isolation. It is one of three layers of the
        methodology, and each layer has standing only in relation to the
        other two.
      </p>

      <ol class="reinforce" data-reveal>
        <li>
          <span class="reinforce__num">01</span>
          <div class="reinforce__body">
            <h3>The curriculum forms the operator who applies the framework.</h3>
            <p>An operator who has not been through the eight phases cannot legitimately run a CROWD POWERED engagement. The curriculum is what makes the framework usable in the field rather than admirable on the page.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="reinforce__num">02</span>
          <div class="reinforce__body">
            <h3>The framework gives the curriculum a venture to ground in.</h3>
            <p>Without the twelve-step framework, the eight phases are general-purpose business education. With it, every course is taught against the question of how the venture will be structured to refuse single-principal risk and to reinvest ninety percent of revenue back into itself.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="reinforce__num">03</span>
          <div class="reinforce__body">
            <h3>VERIDEX is the audit standard the plan is held to.</h3>
            <p>The business plan written across the eight phases is not the end of the story. It is the document the validation layer measures against, period over period, on twenty-two gates. The curriculum produces the plan; the framework structures the venture; VERIDEX confirms whether either is performing as written.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* ──────────────────────────────────────────────
      §05 — Read further
      ────────────────────────────────────────────── */}
  <section class="section section--ink">
    <div class="frame">
      <SectionMarker num="§ 05" tag="Read further" inverse />

      <div class="next-row" data-reveal>
        <a href="/methodology/framework" class="next-link">
          <span class="next-link__num">01</span>
          <span class="next-link__label">CROWD POWERED &mdash; the twelve-step framework</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/methodology/validation" class="next-link">
          <span class="next-link__num">03</span>
          <span class="next-link__label">VERIDEX &mdash; the validation layer</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/methodology" class="next-link">
          <span class="next-link__num">&larr;</span>
          <span class="next-link__label">Back to methodology overview</span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* ─── shared section vocabulary, matched to /methodology/framework ─── */
  .section { padding: 96px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule); }
  .section:last-of-type { border-bottom: none; }
  .section--paper-deep { background: var(--paper-deep); }
  .section--ink { background: var(--ink); color: var(--paper); border-bottom: none; }

  .s-title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: clamp(28px, 3.4vw, 42px);
    line-height: 1.15;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    margin: 0 0 18px;
    max-width: 28ch;
    color: var(--ink);
  }
  .section--ink .s-title { color: var(--paper); }
  .s-lede {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 18px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--subtext);
    max-width: 64ch;
    margin: 0 0 40px;
  }
  .prose { max-width: 680px; font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--ink-soft); }
  .prose p { margin: 0 0 24px; }
  .prose em { color: var(--ink); font-style: italic; }

  /* ─── §02 The map: 8-cell horizontal timeline ─── */
  .map {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    border: 1px solid var(--ink);
    background: var(--paper);
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(8, 1fr);
  }
  .map__cell {
    border-right: 1px solid var(--ink);
  }
  .map__cell:last-child { border-right: none; }
  @media (max-width: 1024px) {
    .map { grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr); }
    .map__cell:nth-child(4n) { border-right: none; }
    .map__cell:nth-child(-n+4) { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--ink); }
  }
  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .map { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); }
    .map__cell:nth-child(4n) { border-right: 1px solid var(--ink); }
    .map__cell:nth-child(2n) { border-right: none; }
    .map__cell:nth-last-child(-n+2) { border-bottom: none; }
    .map__cell:not(:nth-last-child(-n+2)) { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--ink); }
  }
  .map__link {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 12px;
    padding: 28px 18px 24px;
    text-decoration: none;
    color: var(--ink);
    height: 100%;
    transition: background 200ms ease;
  }
  .map__link:hover { background: var(--paper-deep); }
  .map__num {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--oxblood);
  }
  .map__name {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: 17px;
    line-height: 1.25;
    color: var(--ink);
  }

  /* ─── §03 Phases in full ─── */
  .phases {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 56px;
  }
  .phase {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
    padding-top: 36px;
  }
  .phase:first-child { border-top: 1px solid var(--ink); }
  .phase__head { margin-bottom: 20px; }
  .phase__index {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 14px;
    margin-bottom: 14px;
  }
  .phase__num {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: 32px;
    line-height: 1;
    color: var(--oxblood);
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }
  .phase__course {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--subtext);
  }
  .phase__name {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: clamp(24px, 2.6vw, 30px);
    line-height: 1.2;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin: 0 0 12px;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }
  .phase__resolves {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: var(--subtext);
    margin: 0;
    max-width: 72ch;
  }
  .phase__resolves-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin-right: 8px;
  }
  .phase__body {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 17px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    max-width: 72ch;
    margin: 0 0 28px;
  }

  .phase__detail {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 2fr 1fr;
    gap: 36px;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
    padding-top: 24px;
  }
  @media (max-width: 800px) {
    .phase__detail { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 28px; }
  }
  .phase__sub-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--oxblood);
    margin: 0 0 14px;
  }
  .phase__topics {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    columns: 2;
    column-gap: 28px;
  }
